"The beer pours a nice mahogany color, with ruby highlights. Decent clarity. A thin beige head disappears quickly, leaving no lacing or collar. Lively carbonation continues to stream to the surface in tiny jets. Not much in the nose. A little caramel malt, faint cherry and a macro-lager scent. The flavor is a mixed bag. There's a touch of brown sugar sweetness and a tame hop profile. Even with generous gulp sloshing around my mouth, there's not much to hold on to in the flavor department. Ever-so-hidden touch of brown ale nuttiness. That's about it. Behind it all, there's a slight roughness to the alcohol content. Marginally solvent-like. The carbonation is very prickly and it masks the thinness of the beer a little. Well, Mom, I don't see myself picking this one up ever again. It should work just fine for poker swill tonight, but that's the extent of my plans for this beer."
""
""
"Poured from a brown 12 oz. bottle. Has a pretty amber/brown color with a 1/2 inch head. Smell is of malts, some sweetness. Taste is malty, sugar, a bit of nuttiness. Feels medium bodied in the mouth and overall is an easy drinking and decent beer."
