"Medium brown pour with an open light tan head that dissipates quickly with no lacing. Smell is almost nonexistent. Traces of caramel and nut a bit of cracker. Taste follows this recipe. Light biscuit, caramel and a hint if nuttiness. Light body. In its entirety the light body and rather nondescript flavor give this a watery quality. I don't know what part if this is 'Abbey'. It's drinkable but not something I'd ever seek out."
